==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Murexide
<hw>Mu*rex"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>murex</ets> the purple fish, purple.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A crystalline nitrogenous substance (<chform>C8H8N6O6</chform>,
<chname>5-5'-nitrilodibarbituric acid monoammonium salt</chname>) having
a splendid dichroism, being green by reflected light and garnet-red by
transmitted light. It was formerly used in dyeing calico, and was
obtained in a large quantities from guano. It is now synthesized from
alloxan. Formerly called also <altname>ammonium
purpurate</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Murexoin</ent>⟦br⟧
